The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Bernard Bagans interim coach 

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: Bernard Operanhozie will be the makeshift coach for Mohun Bagan in the rest of the season. Announcing the Nigerians appointment to the hot seat following Chima Okeries resignation, the club said that Bernard would be assisted by Bhaichung Bhutia and Jose Ramirez Barreto. 

Mohun Bagan are scheduled to play three AFC Cup and six National Football League matches this season. 

This was decided after the clubs executive committee meeting on Thursday evening. Well not appoint a full-time new coach this season. We have asked Bernanrd to take charge and he will coach the side in consultation with Bhaichung and Barreto, said Mohun Bagan secretary Anjan Mitra. 

Mitra also rued that they were yet to recieve their share of funds from gate sells during the last three NFLs and demanded that they be allowed to host home matches in the Pro League. 




